-- China shares have biggest gain in 2 months, property lifts
-- By Clement Tan
-- Wed Jan 22, 2014 02:06AM EST
-- None



HONG KONG, Jan 22 (Reuters) - China shares had their best day in two months on Wednesday as volumes surged, with the battered property sector leading an extension of a rebound as cash rates eased further in the mainland.

The CSI300 <.CSI300> of the biggest Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings ended up 2.6 percent at 2,243.8 points, while the Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> climbed 2.2 percent. The gains were the biggest in a single day since Nov. 18, and helped the indexes bounce further from multi-month lows recorded on Monday. [ID:nL3N0KW1H8] Gains came in the strongest Shanghai volumes since Dec. 16 that was also nearly 40 percent above its 20-day moving average.